    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="813"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d813">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.62/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 6, 3.55
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5002. Foreign Office informs me that I and my staff will not be permitted to
                    leave Germany until definite information is received regarding arrangements made
                    for departure of <persName corresp="#p_BJHC1">Count Bernstorff</persName> and
                    his staff from the United States. Please answer urgently with full details also
                    as to consuls. Foreign Office will send cable to <persName corresp="#p_BJHC1"
                        >Bernstorff</persName> in cipher which censor at Sayville has and hopes it
                    will be delivered. We are not allowed to telegraph to our consuls until we hear
                    your dispositions what [<hi rend="italic">as to</hi>] German consuls then on
                        [<hi rend="italic">return</hi>]. Reports here German ships and crews have
                    been seized, and Foreign Office says prisoners on <hi rend="italic"
                        >Yarrowdale</hi> will not be released until news comes that these reports
                    are not true.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
